frameDefinitions: A Lessor who owns some Goods allows a Lessee to use the Goods temporarily in exchange for Money.
A Period or Eventuality is related to its Duration.
An Agent affects a Patient in such a way that the Patient (or some Subregion of the Patient) ends up in a non-canonical state.
A Lessee gains the use of Goods owned by a Lessor by payment to the Lessor.
The Lender gives the Theme to the Borrower with the expectation that the Borrower will return the Theme to the Lender after a Duration of time.
frameExamples: We are <t>renting</t> our apartment from a kind man named Tom.
I am <t>lending</t> a student of mine my book on German modal particles.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Lessee</fen> has <fen>Money</fen> and wants the <fen>Goods</fen>.
The role <fen>Goods</fen> is the item which is temporarily exchanged for <fen>Money</fen>.
The <fen>Lessor</fen> has possession of the <fen>Goods</fen> and temporarily exchanges them for <fen>Money</fen> from a <fen>Lessee</fen>.
The time at which the renting takes place.
The location where the leasing takes place.

A situation, action or event whose duration is being described.  The <fen>Eventuality</fen> occurs as the External Argument if the adjective is used predicatively, or as the modified noun if the adjective is used attributively:
Sometimes a period of time, rather than an event or state is described.
The amount of time that the <fen>Eventuality</fen>, <fen>Period</fen>, or <fen>Entity</fen> lasts.

An item which is metonymically related to an <fen>Eventuality</fen>.  Some common eventualities that are metonymically entailed are the effect of the entity in its capacity as an instrument and the existence of the entity.
The conscious entity, generally a person, that performs the intentional action that results in the damage to the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The entity which is affected by the <fen>Agent</fen> so that it is damaged.
An event which leads to the damage of the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> damages the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the location of the scene where a <fen>Agent</fen> damages a <fen>Patient</fen>.
The individual that gains temporary use of the <fen>Goods</fen> by paying the <fen>Lessor</fen>
The role <fen>Goods</fen> is an item which is temporarily exchanged for <fen>Money</fen> in a transaction.
When the event occurs.
The location the renting takes place.
The person or institution who receives the <fen>Theme</fen> from the <fen>Lender</fen> for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The person or institution who gives the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Borrower</fen> for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The object that is transferred from the <fen>Lender</fen> to the <fen>Borrower</fen> for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time when the lending event occurs.
The location in which the Lender lends the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Borrower</fen>.

I lent <fex>the book</fex> to him for a whole month, and he still hasn't read it.
